<paragraph blockId="23.[140,1108,167,1249]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
There are least three known undescribed species: one recorded here, one from off the South Island of 
<collectingCountry box="[379,536,976,1003]" name="New Zealand" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce NL" box="[554,695,976,1002]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" pagination="453 - 466" refId="ref22653" refString="Bruce NL (2008) Two new deep-water species of Caecoserolis Wagele, 1994 (Isopoda, Sphaeromatidea, Serolidae) from off North Island, New Zealand. Zootaxa 1866: 453 - 466." type="journal article" year="2008">Bruce 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and the species from off 
<collectingCountry name="Norfolk Island" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">Norfolk Island</collectingCountry>
recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore GCB &amp; Brandt A" box="[363,658,1011,1038]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" pagination="151 - 168" refId="ref23549" refString="Poore GCB, Brandt A (1997) Crustacea Isopoda Serolidae: Acutiserolis cidaris and Caecoserolis novaecaledoniae, two new species from the Coral Sea. Resultats de Campagnes MU- SORSTOM, Volume 18. Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris 176: 151 - 168." type="journal article" year="1997">Poore and Brandt (1997)</bibRefCitation>
; a further six probable new species are known from around 
<collectingCountry box="[376,529,1047,1073]" name="New Zealand" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode box="[543,622,1047,1073]" country="New Zealand" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/nyq3-3g6s" name="National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" type="Other institutional type">NIWA</collectionCode>
NIC collections, personal observation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="40" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[140,1108,167,1249]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,344,1081,1107]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis box="[185,339,1081,1107]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The genus is known from the Western Indian Ocean eastwards to 
<collectingCountry box="[140,177,1117,1143]" name="Fiji" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">Fiji</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[234,389,1117,1144]" name="New Zealand" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, the Southern Ocean and the northern Coral Sea in the Gulf of Papua; at depths from 700 to 3184 metres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[140,1108,167,1249]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,320,1187,1213]" pageId="23" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis box="[185,315,1187,1213]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="40" reason="1">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
From the Greek ‘myopia’ in combination with [Se]-rolis; alluding the tiny or absent eyes. Gender neuter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
